╭─ Assistant [MainThread@3685931] ─────────────────────────────╮
│ This patch addresses an assertion failure in the loop        │
│ vectorizer when handling a PHI node that merges two          │
│ loop-invariant values from different control flow paths      │
│ within the loop.                                             │
│                                                              │
│ The root cause is that when `VPRecipeBuilder::tryToBlend`    │
│ encounters a PHI node where one of the incoming values comes │
│ from a dominating predecessor (and thus has no associated    │
│ edge mask), it incorrectly assumes all incoming values must  │
│ be identical and stops processing. This is not true when the │
│ PHI node is blending different loop-invariant values based   │
│ on control flow.                                             │
│                                                              │
│ The fix modifies `VPRecipeBuilder::tryToBlend` to correctly  │
│ handle this scenario. When an incoming value has no edge     │
│ mask (indicating it's from a dominating block), the logic    │
│ now continues to process the other incoming values, which    │
│ will have edge masks. This ensures that a `VPBlendRecipe` is │
│ properly constructed with the correct masked operands,       │
│ leading to a valid VPlan and fixing the crash.               │
│                                                              │
│ Additionally, the `handleReplication` function is updated to │
│ delegate non-header PHI nodes to `tryToBlend`, which is the  │
│ correct handler for such cases. This improves the code's     │
│ structure and ensures PHI nodes are processed by the         │
│ appropriate logic.                                           │
│                                                              │
│ ```diff                                                      │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp        │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp        │
│ @@ -8250,10 +8250,12 @@                                      │
│      VPValue *EdgeMask =                                     │
│          getEdgeMask(Phi->getIncomingBlock(In),              │
│ Phi->getParent());                                           │
│      if (!EdgeMask) {                                        │
│ +      // If there is no edge mask, the incoming block is    │
│ the dominating                                               │
│ +      // predecessor. This is the first operand of the      │
│ blend.                                                       │
│        assert(In == 0 && "Both null and non-null edge masks  │
│ found");                                                     │
│ -      assert(all_equal(Operands) &&                         │
│ -             "Distinct incoming values with one having a    │
│ full mask");                                                 │
│ -      break;                                                │
│ +      if (all_equal(Operands))                              │
│ +        break;                                              │
│ +      continue;                                             │
│      }                                                       │
│      OperandsWithMask.push_back(EdgeMask);                   │
│    }                                                         │
│ @@ -8436,8 +8438,10 @@                                       │
│    }                                                         │
│  }                                                           │
│                                                              │
│ -VPReplicateRecipe                                           │
│ *VPRecipeBuilder::handleReplication(Instruction *I,          │
│ -                                                            │
│ VFRange &Range) {                                            │
│ +VPRecipeBase                                                │
│ *VPRecipeBuilder::handleReplication(Instruction *I, VFRange  │
│ &Range) {                                                    │
│ +  if (auto *Phi = dyn_cast<PHINode>(I))                     │
│ +    return tryToBlend(Phi, mapToVPValues(I->operands()));   │
│ +                                                            │
│    bool IsUniform =                                          │
│ LoopVectorizationPlanner::getDecisionAndClampRange(          │
│        [&](ElementCount VF) { return                         │
│ CM.isUniformAfterVectorization(I, VF); },                    │
│        Range);                                               │
│                                                              │
│ ```                                                          │
